    <p>  For best Aglio E Olio, Opt for freshly peeled garlic cloves in this preparation, finely chopped with a knife. While few opt for sliced garlic, our preference leans towards minced garlic for optimal results. I advise against grating or using a garlic press, as these methods could lead to the garlic turning into a paste when saut√©ed in oil. Extra virgin olive oil is the main ingredient in this recipe so, try to get a good quality one if you can; spaghetti aglio e olio won't taste good if your oil is low quality or rancid. For pasta selection, I suggest opting for a long pasta variety, preferably bronze-cut as indicated on the packaging. This type's coarse and textured surface adheres more effectively to the sauce. Suitable options include spaghetti, linguine, bavette, bucatini, tagliatelle, fettuccine, and even angel hair pasta. If you require a gluten-free option, go for gluten-free spaghetti.</p>
